President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Dale Cabaniss of Virginia for the position of Director of the Office of Personnel Management for a four-year term. Cabaniss has previously served as Chairman of the Federal Labor Relations Authority and has over 20 years of experience in the United States Senate, where she oversaw civil service issues on the Committee on Governmental Affairs and the Committee on Appropriations. Cabaniss holds a B.A. from the University of Georgia and a J.D. from the Catholic University of America.